  "description": "Replacement of peak shaving generators.",
  "enriched_description": "Multi-year program to replace ~10.5 MW of aging generation assets (end of useful life) that reduce wholesale power costs by avoiding coincident peak demand charges. Latest: 4,000 kW natural gas generator at ECU Health Science Campus ($3.9M, Gregory Poole Power Systems) saving ~$88,640/month. Previously completed: 1,000 kW at P&G Substation, 1,500 kW at Mayne Pharma. Industrial-scale load management demonstrates GUC's capability to serve large users like Boviet (4 MW peak-shaving included in substation deal). Program runs through 6/30/2027 - watch for additional generator installations as industrial base grows.",
